Job Description:
Duties
Provide genetic counseling to patients to include risk assessment, psychosocial support, referral to local support resources for continuity of care, and comprehensive psychosocial support to affected families;
Develop clinical research studies to include quantitative or qualitative research, intervention studies exploring alternative approaches to genetic counseling; development of assessment and treatment tools for psychosocial needs;
Plan and develop protocols to include recommending or modifying methods and procedures, determines deficiencies in methodology or protocols and takes appropriate corrective action, and evaluate new or unfamiliar methods and protocols;
Perform studies on the heritability and psychological consequences of genetic diseases and organizes the integration of pertinent medical, genetic, and psychosocial information relevant to the subjects and protocols;
